### Root Layout

The `app/layout.js` file defines the root layout shared by all pages. It is **required** in the App Router:

```jsx
// app/layout.js
export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>
        <nav>Global Nav</nav>
        {children}
        <footer>Global Footer</footer>
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

### Nested Layouts

Each folder can have its own `layout.js` that wraps all pages in that segment:

```jsx
// app/dashboard/layout.js
export default function DashboardLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <section>
      <aside>Dashboard Sidebar</aside>
      <main>{children}</main>
    </section>
  );
}
```

Layouts are **nested** — the child layout renders inside the parent layout.

### Template.js

Unlike `layout.js`, `template.js` creates a new instance for each navigation (mounts/unmounts):

```jsx
// app/dashboard/template.js
'use client';

export default function Template({ children }) {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);

  return (
    <div>
      <p>Count resets on navigation: {count}</p>
      <button onClick={() => setCount(c => c + 1)}>+</button>
      {children}
    </div>
  );
}
```

### Layout Props

Layouts receive:
- `children` — the page or nested layout content
- `params` — route parameters (server components only)

```jsx
// app/blog/[slug]/layout.js
export default function BlogLayout({ children, params }) {
  return (
    <article>
      <h2>Blog Post: {params.slug}</h2>
      {children}
    </article>
  );
}
```

### Metadata API

Export metadata or generateMetadata from layouts or pages:

```jsx
// app/layout.js
export const metadata = {
  title: 'My App',
  description: 'Generated by Next.js',
};

// Dynamic metadata
export async function generateMetadata({ params }) {
  const post = await getPost(params.slug);
  return {
    title: post.title,
    description: post.excerpt,
  };
}
```

codeExample:
// app/layout.js — Root layout with metadata
export const metadata = {
  title: {
    default: 'My App',
    template: '%s | My App',
  },
  description: 'A Next.js application',
};

export default function RootLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>{children}</body>
    </html>
  );
}

// app/dashboard/layout.js — Nested layout
export default function DashboardLayout({ children }) {
  return (
    <div style={{ display: 'flex' }}>
      <nav style={{ width: 200 }}>Sidebar</nav>
      <main>{children}</main>
    </div>
  );
}
